Document: VSlider
Path: godot/classes/class_vslider.rst
Summary: A vertical slider control for adjusting values along a vertical axis, inheriting from Range and operating in the opposite direction of VScrollBar.

A vertical slider, used to adjust a value by moving a grabber along a vertical axis. It is a Range-based control and goes from bottom (min) to top (max). Note that this direction is the opposite of VScrollBar's. Inherits: Range < Control < CanvasItem < Node < Object. Key Rule: Vertical movement increases value from bottom to top, unlike VScrollBar which increases from top to bottom.
---CHUNK---
Document: VSlider
Path: godot/classes/class_vslider.rst
Summary: Horizontal and vertical size flags for VSlider that override Control class defaults.

- size_flags_horizontal (bitfield: SizeFlags): Overrides Control's horizontal size flags. Default: 0
- size_flags_vertical (bitfield: SizeFlags): Overrides Control's vertical size flags. Default: 1